The paper deals with algorithmic pricing, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and involves the allocation of resources (cs.DS). The use of valuations and the objective of revenue maximization suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses competitive equilibrium and envy-free pricing, which are concepts in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the use of algorithms to solve the revenue-maximizing problem suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
